plotInformation.title: World Organization Membership by Country
plotInformation.caption: This plot shows the overlap of world organization membership by country. Notably, most countries, 143, are part of the world organizations (WTO, UN, WHO, Interpol, and UNESCO) and an additional 32 are part of these organizations and NATO. There are 22 countries that are not part of any of these organizations.
